  "text": "Three engineered tissue were then placed into the window chamber, in direct contact with the exposed subdermal tissue. Care was taken to avoid placing the tissues in direct contact with arterioles or venules, as doing so can confound accurate quantification of blood flow and pO 2 . To enable quantification of pO 2 , *100 mL of 5 · 10 -6 M Oxyphor G4 dissolved in sterile saline was injected into the window chamber. [CITATION_1] The chamber was closed by placing a 12 mm cover slip into the window of the frame. Following the surgical procedure, buprenorphine was administered (0.1 mg/kg administered via i.p. injection). Mice were imaged once per day for 14 days. After all imaging was completed, mice were sacrificed via pentobarbital overdose.",
